RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 71. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLUBHOUSE BRIDE dueled briefly outside WHERE IS ZIZI then cleared early, angled into the two path entering the turn, asked right handed past the three-sixteenths pole and powered away from the runner-up. WHERE IS ZIZI broke well to take the early lead then ceded command to CLUBHOUSE BRIDE, chased that rival three wide through the turn, was no match for the winner in the stretch run but was clearly second best. CANDY KENDALL chased three wide out of range into the turn, moved into the two path around the bend, tipped four wide into the stretch and outkicked LOVME LIKEAFOOL for the show honors. LOVME LIKEAFOOL chased two wide leaving the backstretch, moved to the rail around the bend, tipped back to the two path approaching the stretch and got edged for the show. MUMBLES BROCKMAN broke a step slow, traveled at the back three wide exiting the backstretch, moved out around the bend and failed to menace. SIGNORA VITTORIA broke a bit slow on the outside, raced outside a rival four wide into the turn, entered the lane six wide and was not a factor.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ESCAPE ROUTE raced up close two wide into the turn, angled six wide around the bend, rallied widest and drew alongside the top pair past the eight pole, took over past the sixteenth pole and drew clear near the wire. IT'S MY HOUSE pressed the pace from outside, moved up on even terms around the bend, got carried wide approaching the stretch, battled down the lane, put a nose in front briefly at the sixteenth pole but was outkicked by the winner late. MANITOWISH chased three then two wide on the turn, rallied inside the leaders and gained the show. PRINCIPE CARLO bumped inner rival soon after the start, set the pace under pressure from IT'S MY HOUSE, dueled with that rival around the bend, drifted out approaching the stretch, fought head to head into the final furlong, relinquished the lead at the sixteenth pole and yielded late. PHOSPHORESCENCE (FR) bumped with PRINCIPE CARLO then got crowded between rivals early and dropped back to last, saved ground through the turn, finished willingly but could only whittle the gap late.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: SATOSHI took a bump from BLUE CLOUD at the start, went up to press from inside, took over early on the turn, cleared outer rivals late on the bend, drifted out in the lane and drew away late. BAJAN BASHERT prompted the pace three deep to the turn, vied four deep around the bend, chased after SATOSHI six wide into the drive, drifted inward and hand to alter in further when coming up behind the leader, then faltered in deep stretch. PLUM CREEK stumbled leaving the gate, chased off the rail early, put in a mild bid between rivals around the bend, could not kick on with SATOSHI past the five-sixteenths pole and flattened in the furlong grounds. BLUE CLOUD veered in and bumped the winner in the beginning, trailed two wide through the turn and failed to make an impact. C'MON LETS SWITCH away quickly while rank setting the early the pace with rivals on both sides, lost command early on the turn, fought three deep midway around the bend, could not keep up with the winner and chased five wide into the lane, then faded in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 62. Maiden Claiming Purse 23000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DIAL A FRIEND set the pace three deep early, cleared around the bend, showed the way three wide into the stretch, roused at the three-sixteenths pole and widened through the final furlong. HIGH FLYING GRACIE chased along the inside, had to pause briefly when in a bit tight approaching the three-eighths pole, cut the corner into the lane, churned on down the lane and shared the place honors with COCONUT GIRL. COCONUT GIRL stalked off the inside, spun five wide into the lane, finished willingly and could not be separated from HIGH FLYING GRACIE for second. JAZZY EMPRESS raced up close on the inside, chased two then three wide on the turn, angled out in upper stretch and lacked a rally. POP CHART chased three wide into the turn, four wide into the lane and weakened. ALMOST GOT LUCKY forced out by LOVE HONOR AND PAY at the start, chased five, six, then seven wide on the turn and was not a factor. VHAGAR vied for the lead inside DIAL A FRIEND to the turn, chased two wide around the bend and came up empty in the lane. LOVE HONOR AND PAY veered out leaving the gate, tracked four wide into the turn, exited the bend five wide and failed to menace.

ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, chased 2-3wide, angled out upper, no rally

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GRAZEN TOUCH chased five deep between rivals early then four wide into the turn, raced six wide turning for home, rallied to the front midstretch and bested SHE'S MUY MUY in deep stretch. CY'S SILKSTOCKING broke inward then went up to fight for the lead from inside, cleared into the turn, led along the rail then two wide into the drive, drifted out to the middle portion of the track, lost command midstretch and weakened late. RACE.FOOTNOTES: IRISH WAHINE stalked the pace along the rail into the turn, two wide into the stretch, rallied from inside to challenge with a furlong left to run and drove clear in the final sixteenth. NEVER SWAY vied with rivals then inched ahead and showed the way three wide into the turn, maintained a short lead around the bend then cleared past the five-sixteenths pole, threatened by IRISH WAHINE entering the final furlong and got outkicked in deep stretch. FLATTERWITHJEWELS showed early speed between rivals then took hold to cede command, chased three to four wide around the bend and finished evenly in the late stages. JACRODRA'S DEVIL vied for the lead inside rivals, fought through the turn and down the lane and weakened late. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Soviet Problem S. LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 1M Dirt CR: 84. Stakes Purse 100000. FOR GOLDEN STATE SERIES ELGIBLE CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. By subscription of $100 each, which shall accompany the nomination, on or before November 30th 2023 closed with 7 or by supplementary nomination of $1,000 each by c losing time of entries for Golden State eligible horses. (Non Golden State eligible horses, $25,000 to Supplement - Such horse shall not have to pay starting fee and will be automatically eligible to all future Golden State Series Stakes, subject only tor egular nomination and starter fees. $500 to enter and an additional $1,000 to start, with $100,000 guaranteed of which $60,000 to the winner $20,000 to second, $12,000 to third, $6,000 to fourth, $2,000 to fifth, Weight:123 lbs. Non winners of $60,000 tt wice allowed 2 lbs., such a race 4 lbs., non winners of a race other than maiden, claiming or starter allowed 6 lbs., Starters to be named through the entry box by closing time of entries. A trophy will be presented to the winning owner. Nominations Close
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MADISON RAE took control early from inside, set the pace under pressure up the backstretch, fought with outer rivals around the far turn, inched ahead at the top of the lane, cleared midstretch and held gamely to the wire. LORETTA LYNN broke a step slow, chased along the four path on the clubhouse turn, bid three deep at the three-eighths pole, five wide into the lane, failed to find the needed late kick in the furlongs grounds but edged ASADA FRIES for the place honors. ASADA FRIES chased in the two path through both turns, bumped repeatedly with PETIT FILET near the three-sixteenths pole, finished willingly late but got edged by LORETTA LYNN for second. PETIT FILET stalked three wide early, moved up to apply pressure from outside in the middle stages, vied between three then four wide on the second bend, bumped repeatedly with ASADA FRIES near the three-sixteenths pole and weakened in the late stages. PUTT FOR DOUGH toss her head, veered out and almost lost her rider at the start, GUTIERREZ managed to regain his right iron and trailed three then four wide on the clubhouse turn, chased within range on second turn two, three, then four wide but flattened out in the lane. THE RIDER OF PETIT FILET LODGED AN OBJECTION AGAINST ASADA FRIES FOR ALLEGED INTERFERENCE IN THE STRETCH. FOLLOWING A REVIEW, THE STEWARDS RULED THAT BOTH RIVALS CONTRIBUTED TO THE INCIDENT AND NO CHANGE WOULD BE MADE.

ENTRY.OWNER: Rodas III Victor M Rodas Holly and Garcia Oscar L
